#Germline risk: Predicted transcriptomic score (PTRS) This is the code to generate the predicted transcriptomic risk score and assess its ability to prognosticate overall survival and progression free survival among breast cancer patients.

The predicted transcriptomic score is derived from using the weight of a genes association to germline risk of breast cancer * predicted expression of that gene, summed across different thresholds of signifcance.

#PTRS-Overall survival in breast cancer

We see an association between PTRS (predicted transcriptomic) score and overall survival. This score incorporates the germline in both genes associated with risk (by weights) and in terms of the predicted transcriptome.

#Control for Predicted-TPRS score - overall transcriptome and overall survival

The risk weights that are used to add effect sizes to the gene per the score add to the significance of the score.

#PTRS-Progression-free survival in breast cancer
